page.title: 08LANDSCAPE
page.content: Our square's one in a part of Devon called the South Hams. The landscape is very hilly, there is hardly any flat ground here.We don't have any stone walls surounding the fields, instead we have hedges and trees. There are many green lanes such as Coplands and Jackmans lanes where there are Devon banks, which are small walls covered with earth and with hedgerows on top and wild flowers all the way up.They are often 5 or 6 metres high.There are large areas of woodland, some coniferous and some of mixed trees.It is an area of countryside containing many farms.
